<section id="approach" class="core-insight">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="eyebrow">THE APPROACH</p>
    <h2 class="heading">Three lenses into one semantic index</h2>
    <p class="body">
      ChunkHound parses your code with cAST — AST-aware chunking backed by
      Carnegie Mellon research (<a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2506.15655" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="paper-link"><code>arXiv:2506.15655</code></a>). It builds a semantic graph that search, research,
      and documentation all draw from. Not three separate tools — three lenses into one index.
    </p>

    <div class="lens-row">
      <div class="lens-card">
        <span class="lens-name">Search</span>
        <span class="lens-desc">Find code semantically</span>
      </div>
      <div class="lens-card">
        <span class="lens-name">Research</span>
        <span class="lens-desc">Understand architecture</span>
      </div>
      <div class="lens-card">
        <span class="lens-name">Autodoc</span>
        <span class="lens-desc">Generate documentation</span>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="hub">
      <div class="hub-line"></div>
      <div class="hub-node">One semantic index</div>
      <div class="hub-line"></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
